



 - cli command / script that copies specific file to dotfiles repo
    - full path relative to $HOME is maintained (~/dotfiles/ == ~/)
 - post-commit apply hook
 - bi-directional: 
    - from repo copy to appropriate locations
    - update specific file(s) or all files into repo
    - changes always forced overwrite
 - utilize a json path map from dotfiles repo to real file location when os specific differences exist

 - more interactive install script
    - determine if work or personal machine
        - affects things like .gitconfig
    - confirm what package manager to use
    - check/uncheck packages
    - collect software that failed to install and provide list of success and failures to user
